-- Carmax posts loss
-- 
-- Fri Dec 19, 2008 8:31am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/19/us-carmax-idUSTRE4BI2ZZ20081219

 

 (Reuters) - Carmax Inc ( KMX.N ) on Friday reported third-quarter sales fell 23 percent to $1.46 billion. 

 * Q3 loss per share $0.10 * Q3 same store sales fell 24 percent * Qtrly total used unit sales decreased 17% * Reuters Estimates Q3 earnings per share view $0.00, revenue view $1,556.14 million * Says Q3 results reduced by $0.12 per share for Carmax auto finance unfavorable items * Says currently evaluating variety of alternatives to preserve sales associated with caf origination channel * Says remain in compliance with financial covenants contained in warehouse and revolving credit facilities * Says do not believe can make a meaningful projection of fiscal 2009 earnings * Says now decided to temporarily suspend store growth